I&#39;d recommend using the patch decorator. It will automatically replace the function with a Mock object, so you don&#39;t have to import and change it manually.

The mock will be passed as a parameter to the decorated test abd it will be local. Once the function is over the Mock is removed and the original function restored.

```python
from unittest.mock import patch
from testing_print import hello

@patch(&#39;testing_print.hello.sample_greet1&#39;, return_value=&#39;Prasad&#39;)
def test_greet1(mock):
    s = hello.greet1()
    assert s == &#39;Prasad&#39;
```

