&gt; A full binary tree (sometimes referred to as a proper or plane binary tree) is a tree in which every node has either 0 or 2 children. 

You could define this in Isabelle like this:


    datatype tree = 
          Empty 
        | Node (left:tree) (elem:nat) (right:tree)
    
    fun full where
      &quot;full Empty = True                                          ― ‹Not sure - is the empty tree full?›&quot;
    | &quot;full (Node Empty x Empty) = True                           ― ‹Case for 0 children›&quot;
    | &quot;full (Node l x r) = (l≠Empty ∧ r≠Empty ∧ full l ∧ full r)  ― ‹Case for 2 children›&quot;

